Biology . The larvae live on macrophytes in lakes and marshes, feeding on the cell contents of filamentous algae (
Ito & Kawamura 1980
). The life cycle is univoltine, the first 4 larval instars taking about 10 months to complete development in Hokkaido, northern Japan (
Ito & Kawamura 1980
).
